Based on practical examples, the subject gives an overview of how the clinical pharmacist can participate in the monitoring of drug concentrations and optimize drug dosing schemes based on this. Students solve a sample task as homework. In the webinar, there will be a discussion based on a sample task.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the subject is to provide an overview of the principles of drug concentration monitoring and to provide skills in using knowledge and optimizing drug dosing.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the subject: * knows the principles of drug concentration monitoring * can give practical recommendations for monitoring the plasma concentration of the drug and adjusting the doses of the drugs according to the results of the analysis * knows the reasons that can affect drug concentrations.
